commitResults.messageBody:
Added help messages. The standard help message with no arguement prints
a list of commands and what they do. The second help message prints the
information for a specified command.

Added Parser support for the help command.
abstract class Command has an additional attribute MESSAGE_USAGE, which
is the message printed on how the command is used.
Added MESSAGE_USAGE for ExitCommand
Added line in welcome message to tell users to use help command if
unsure

Forgot that i changed help message objects to hold the help message
as an attribute. Eliminating the need for a printHelpMessage(Command)
method, which required instantiating those commands in order to print
the MESSAGE_USAGE.

commitResults.messageBody:
Added javadoc comments for Command classes
Also moved LoggerUtil class to duke package

Log only changes to data, or errors preventing correct command execution

Not all command classes have/use logger. They are:
CreateWorkoutCommand - executeCommand will log the execution from the
addWorkout method.
HelpCommand - no need to log, just printing a help message
ListWorkoutsCommand - no need to log, just printing the workouts
DisplayExercisesCommand

Added child classes for Parser.
Renamed Generator Class to CommandManager.
